gomodel:SYNGO_3654  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: It is demonstrated that RIM-BP2 clusters calcium channels to the active zone. The authors use STED microscopy and an antibody against Cav2.1 to show that genetic deletion of RIM-BP2 increases the distance between active zone markers and calcium channels, and electrophysiology to show a modest reduction in release probability. This is in line with findings in the fly NMJ, where removal of RIM-BP leads to a reduction in calcium channel density at the active zone.\n\n3/2/2017 Pim\n- effect on Ca2+ sensitivity of SV release in Fig.3 (no effect found on global Ca2+-concentration)\n- effect on VGCC localization shown in Fig.4\n- effect on synaptic transmission (STP) shown in Fig.2 (and 3). Experimental description: KO Mouse Generation.\n\nRIM-BP2 and RIM-BP1 targeting vector construction and KO mouse generation by standard homologous recombination were performed by genOway." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3654" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

